
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  MISSION: SCHEMATIC RETRIEVAL                                             ║
║  SKILL: find (file location)                                              ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
The ship's schematic archive contains hundreds of files organized into a
complex directory structure. You need to locate specific repair documents
without manually searching every folder.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Locate the Navigation Repair Manual
─────────────────────────────────────────
Based on the log analysis, we need to repair the navigation system.
Somewhere in this directory structure is a file called:

    nav_repair_manual.txt

Find this file and read its contents. It contains a repair code that
you'll need for the next step.

When you find the repair code, run:
    ./verify <code>

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

USEFUL COMMANDS:
    find . -name "filename"        Find exact filename
    find . -name "*.txt"           Find all .txt files
    find . -name "*repair*"        Find files containing "repair"
    find . -type f                 Find only files (not directories)
    find . -type d                 Find only directories

BONUS CHALLENGE:
How many total .txt files are in this directory tree?

    find . -name "*.txt" | wc -l

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

